In Go, anonymous structs can be used to group variables into a single
"namespace" to keep them in one place.

```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"
)

func main() {
	var apiSettings struct {
		port int
		host string
	}
	apiSettings.port = 8000
	fmt.Println(settings)
}
```
